<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/701"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_701_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=e8fa6f490a437bd3212deeef65bf0849&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Zepler Building, Highfield Campus" title="Zepler Building, Highfield Campus (Copyright: ECS)" border="0" width="112" height="150" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2>Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050317090021/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/701">Can machines learn? Find out at PASCAL Challenges Workshop</a></h3><p>A workshop being held in Southampton from 11 to 13 April will investigate the learning power of machines and report advances. The Workshop is organized by the PASCAL Network which is led by  Professor John Shawe-Taylor of the School of Electronics and Computer Science. It will present the results of four challenge projects set over the last year and report on state-of-the-art machine learning.</p></div></div><div class='rightside'>

